HEADWORD: effortful
<hw>effortful</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>requiring great
physical effort. Opposite of <ant>effortless</ant>.</def> [Narrower
terms: <stype>arduous, backbreaking, back-breaking, grueling, gruelling,
hard, heavy, laborious, labourious, punishing, slavish, strenuous,
toilsome</stype>; <stype>exhausting, tiring, wearing, wearying</stype>]
<see>Also See: <er>difficult</er>, <er>hard</er>.</see>⟦br⟧
